Various System Administration scripts meant for a Gentoo OS, but that may run
on other machines.

--- Script listing ---

cryptsetup: Sets up the mappings for multi-layer encryption.

init: 'initramfs' early-userspace (ugh) script.

install: Install a Gentoo system.
install_chroot: Executes for the 'chroot' portion of a Gentoo install.

keyfile: Generate a random-number keyfile.

mount: Mounts a device with multi-layer encryption.

setup: Mounts/formats a Gentoo root filesystem.

umount: Removes mappings for the specified encryption mapping.
